ebusctl
-------

Usage:
 ebusctl [Options] Command [Arguments]

Description:
 'ebusctl' is a tcp/udp socket client for ebusproxy.
  hint: try 'help' for available ebusproxy commands.

Options:

-s | --server	name or ip [localhost]
-p | --port  	port [8888]
-u | --udp   	connect via udp [no]

   | --values
   | --version
-h | --help



$ ebusctl help

commands:
 open      - open ebus connection
 close     - close ebus connection

 send      - write message onto ebus 'send ZZPBSBNNDx'

 forward   - forward ebus messages 'forward [-d] [-s server] [-p port] [filter]'
               filter: ebus sequence; without filter all messages will passed
               server: either ip address or hostname
               port:   target udp port number

 dump      - enable/disable raw data dumping

 log       - change logging level 'log level'

 stop      - shutdown daemon
 quit      - close tcp connection

 help      - print this page



ebusfeed
--------

Usage:
 ebusfeed [Options] /path/dumpfile

Description:
 'ebusfeed' sends hex values from dump file to a pseudo terminal device (pty)

  Example: 1. 'socat -d -d pty,raw,echo=0 pty,raw,echo=0'
            2016/03/19 11:36:58 socat[2347] N PTY is /dev/pts/2
            2016/03/19 11:36:58 socat[2347] N PTY is /dev/pts/3
            2016/03/19 11:36:58 socat[2347] N starting data transfer loop with FDs [5,5] and [7,7]
           2. create symbol links to appropriate devices
            'ln -s /dev/pts/2 /dev/ttyUSB2'
            'ln -s /dev/pts/3 /dev/ttyUSB3'
           3. start ebusproxy: 'ebusproxy -f -n -d /dev/ttyUSB2'
           4. start ebusfeed: 'ebusfeed -d /dev/ttyUSB3 /path/to/ebus_dump.bin'

Options:

-d | --device	link on pseudo terminal device []
-t | --time  	delay between 2 bytes in 'us' [10000]

   | --values
   | --version
-h | --help



For bugs and missing features use github issue system.

The author can be contacted at roland.jax@liwest.at.
